Note: CONTOUR INTEGRATION FOR ZETA FUNCTIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "contour_integrate_zeta" that takes function_type as String, s_real as Float, s_imag as Float, contour_path as String returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Note: Perform contour integration for zeta function analytic continuation
    Note: Uses rectangular or semicircular contours around poles and branch cuts
    Note: Essential for computing ζ(s) in critical strip and left half-plane
    
    Let result be Dictionary[String, Float]
    Set result["real"] to 0.0
    Set result["imag"] to 0.0
    
    If function_type == "zeta_mellin" Then:
        Note: Mellin transform integral for zeta function: ∫ t^s e^(-nt) dt / Γ(s+1)
        Note: Contour integration around branch cut of t^s
        Let integral_result be mellin_contour_integral(s_real, s_imag, contour_path)
        Set result["real"] to integral_result["real"]
        Set result["imag"] to integral_result["imag"]
        
    Otherwise If function_type == "zeta_hankel" Then:
        Note: Hankel contour integral for zeta continuation
        Note: ζ(s) = 1/Γ(s) ∫_H t^{s-1} e^t/(e^t - 1) dt
        Let hankel_result be hankel_contour_integral(s_real, s_imag)
        Set result["real"] to hankel_result["real"]
        Set result["imag"] to hankel_result["imag"]
        
    Otherwise If function_type == "functional_equation" Then:
        Note: Integration for functional equation verification
        Let func_eq_result be functional_equation_integral(s_real, s_imag)
        Set result["real"] to func_eq_result["real"]
        Set result["imag"] to func_eq_result["imag"]
    End If
    
    Return result

Process called "mellin_contour_integral" that takes s_real as Float, s_imag as Float, path as String returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Note: Compute Mellin transform contour integral for zeta function
    Note: Integrates around branch cut of complex power function
    
    Let integral_real be 0.0
    Let integral_imag be 0.0
    
    Note: Set up contour path parameters
    If path == "keyhole" Then:
        Note: Keyhole contour around positive real axis branch cut
        Let epsilon be 0.01  Note: Small radius around branch point
        Let R be 100.0  Note: Large radius for outer contour
        
        Note: Path segments: outer circle + upper ray + inner circle + lower ray
        Let segments be 4
        Let points_per_segment be 500
        
        Note: Outer semicircle from R*e^(iπ) to R*e^(-iπ)
        Let theta be 3.14159265359
        Let theta_step be -2.0 * 3.14159265359 / points_per_segment
        
        Let j be 0
        While j < points_per_segment Do:
            Let current_theta be theta + j * theta_step
            Let t_real be R * MathOps.cosine(current_theta)
            Let t_imag be R * MathOps.sine(current_theta)
            
            Note: Compute t^s = e^(s * ln(t))
            Let ln_t_real be MathOps.natural_logarithm(MathOps.square_root(t_real * t_real + t_imag * t_imag))
            Let ln_t_imag be MathOps.arctangent2(t_imag, t_real)
            
            Let s_ln_t_real be s_real * ln_t_real - s_imag * ln_t_imag
            Let s_ln_t_imag be s_real * ln_t_imag + s_imag * ln_t_real
            
            Let power_real be MathOps.exponential(s_ln_t_real) * MathOps.cosine(s_ln_t_imag)
            Let power_imag be MathOps.exponential(s_ln_t_real) * MathOps.sine(s_ln_t_imag)
            
            Note: Compute integrand: t^{s-1} * e^t / (e^t - 1)
            Let exp_t be MathOps.exponential(t_real) * MathOps.cosine(t_imag)
            Let denominator be exp_t - 1.0
            
            If MathOps.absolute_value(denominator) > 0.001 Then:
                Let integrand_real be power_real * exp_t / denominator
                Let integrand_imag be power_imag * exp_t / denominator
                
                Note: Add contribution with path derivative dt
                Let dt_real be -R * MathOps.sine(current_theta) * theta_step
                Let dt_imag be R * MathOps.cosine(current_theta) * theta_step
                
                Set integral_real to integral_real + integrand_real * dt_real - integrand_imag * dt_imag
                Set integral_imag to integral_imag + integrand_real * dt_imag + integrand_imag * dt_real
            End If
            
            Set j to j + 1
        End While
        
    Otherwise:
        Note: Default rectangular contour
        Set integral_real to s_real * 0.5  Note: Simplified result
        Set integral_imag to s_imag * 0.5
    End If
    
    Let result be Dictionary[String, Float]
    Set result["real"] to integral_real
    Set result["imag"] to integral_imag
    Return result

Process called "hankel_contour_integral" that takes s_real as Float, s_imag as Float returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Note: Compute Hankel contour integral for zeta function analytic continuation
    Note: ζ(s) = Γ(1-s)/(2πi) * ∫_H t^{s-1} e^t/(e^t - 1) dt
    
    Let integral_real be 0.0
    Let integral_imag be 0.0
    
    Note: Hankel contour: starts at +∞, loops around origin, returns to +∞
    Let contour_radius be 0.1
    Let num_points be 1000
    
    Note: Path 1: From large positive real to small circle
    Let t_start be 100.0
    Let t_end be contour_radius
    Let step be -(t_start - t_end) / (num_points / 3)
    
    Let t be t_start
    Let k be 0
    While k < num_points / 3 Do:
        Note: Real axis integration
        Let t_s_minus_1 be MathOps.power(t, s_real - 1.0)
        Let exp_t be MathOps.exponential(t)
        Let denominator be exp_t - 1.0
        
        If denominator > 0.001 Then:
            Let integrand be t_s_minus_1 * exp_t / denominator
            Set integral_real to integral_real + integrand * step
        End If
        
        Set t to t + step
        Set k to k + 1
    End While
    
    Note: Path 2: Small circle around origin
    Let angle_step be 2.0 * 3.14159265359 / (num_points / 3)
    Let angle be 0.0
    
    Set k to 0
    While k < num_points / 3 Do:
        Let t_real be contour_radius * MathOps.cosine(angle)
        Let t_imag be contour_radius * MathOps.sine(angle)
        
        Note: Complex power t^{s-1}
        Let ln_t_real be MathOps.natural_logarithm(contour_radius)
        Let ln_t_imag be angle
        
        Let power_exp_real be (s_real - 1.0) * ln_t_real - s_imag * ln_t_imag
        Let power_exp_imag be (s_real - 1.0) * ln_t_imag + s_imag * ln_t_real
        
        Let power_real be MathOps.exponential(power_exp_real) * MathOps.cosine(power_exp_imag)
        Let power_imag be MathOps.exponential(power_exp_real) * MathOps.sine(power_exp_imag)
        
        Note: Add to integral with proper complex arithmetic
        Let dt_real be -contour_radius * MathOps.sine(angle) * angle_step
        Let dt_imag be contour_radius * MathOps.cosine(angle) * angle_step
        
        Set integral_real to integral_real + power_real * dt_real - power_imag * dt_imag
        Set integral_imag to integral_imag + power_real * dt_imag + power_imag * dt_real
        
        Set angle to angle + angle_step
        Set k to k + 1
    End While
    
    Note: Apply Γ(1-s)/(2πi) factor
    Let gamma_factor_real be 1.0 / (2.0 * 3.14159265359)  Note: Simplified
    Set integral_real to integral_real * gamma_factor_real
    Set integral_imag to integral_imag * gamma_factor_real
    
    Let result be Dictionary[String, Float]
    Set result["real"] to integral_real
    Set result["imag"] to integral_imag
    Return result

Process called "functional_equation_integral" that takes s_real as Float, s_imag as Float returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Note: Verify functional equation through contour integration
    Note: Check ζ(s) = 2^s π^{s-1} sin(πs/2) Γ(1-s) ζ(1-s)
    
    Let verification_result be Dictionary[String, Float]
    
    Note: Compute left side: ζ(s) via series (for Re(s) > 1) or continuation
    Let zeta_s_real be 0.0
    Let zeta_s_imag be 0.0
    
    If s_real > 1.0 Then:
        Note: Use direct series for convergence
        Let n be 1
        While n <= 1000 Do:
            Let n_to_s_real be MathOps.power(n, -s_real) * MathOps.cosine(-s_imag * MathOps.natural_logarithm(n))
            Let n_to_s_imag be MathOps.power(n, -s_real) * MathOps.sine(-s_imag * MathOps.natural_logarithm(n))
            
            Set zeta_s_real to zeta_s_real + n_to_s_real
            Set zeta_s_imag to zeta_s_imag + n_to_s_imag
            Set n to n + 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Note: Use analytic continuation result (simplified)
        Set zeta_s_real to -0.5  Note: ζ(0) = -1/2 as reference
        Set zeta_s_imag to 0.0
    End If
    
    Note: Compute right side of functional equation
    Let pi_power_real be MathOps.power(3.14159265359, s_real - 1.0)
    Let two_power_real be MathOps.power(2.0, s_real)
    
    Note: sin(πs/2) computation
    Let sin_arg be 3.14159265359 * s_real / 2.0
    Let sin_value be MathOps.sine(sin_arg)
    
    Note: Simplified verification (full implementation would need complete gamma function)
    Let rhs_real be two_power_real * pi_power_real * sin_value * 0.5  Note: Approximate
    Let rhs_imag be 0.0
    
    Set verification_result["lhs_real"] to zeta_s_real
    Set verification_result["lhs_imag"] to zeta_s_imag
    Set verification_result["rhs_real"] to rhs_real
    Set verification_result["rhs_imag"] to rhs_imag
    Set verification_result["difference_real"] to zeta_s_real - rhs_real
    Set verification_result["difference_imag"] to zeta_s_imag - rhs_imag
    
    Return verification_result